{"name":"Charmed","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>It is said that the void born, even those confined</p>\n<p>to a stationary orbital station, are touched by their proximity</p>\n<p>to the stars and to the Warp. Such tales attribute unnatural</p>\n<p>luck to the void born, and misfortune for others. Whenever a</p>\n<p>void born character spends a Fate Point (but not burns a Fate</p>\n<p>Point), he rolls 1d10. On a roll of 9 or 10, the Fate Point</p>\n<p>does not count as being spent, even though the character</p>\n<p>gains the chosen benefit.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"charmed","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"void","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"0d1IJiJGJwr4PCXI"}
{"name":"Resourceful","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Characters from post-cataclysmic worlds are</p>\n<p>used to getting by with whatever is at hand&mdash;scavenging</p>\n<p>food, equipment, and whatever else they might need. Post-</p>\n<p>cataclysmic world Characters gain a +10 bonus to Survival</p>\n<p>Tests to obtain potable food and water, and to Tech-Use Tests</p>\n<p>to jury-rig or repair equipment that is not overly advanced, as</p>\n<p>determined by the GM.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"resourceful","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"cataclysmic","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"1dquBnpvdtavbAV5"}
{"name":"Enemies of the Imperium","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>This regiment cannot turn to the</p>\n<p>Departmento Munitorum for supplies. To represent the added</p>\n<p>difficulties of scrounging, stealing, or obtaining supplies</p>\n<p>through whatever treacherous organisation to which the</p>\n<p>regiment now belongs, the regiment begins with a Logistics</p>\n<p>Rating of 0 and suffers a &ndash;10 penalty to Logistics Tests. The</p>\n<p>GM may, at his discretion, modify this value to represent</p>\n<p>the resources of any group to which the regiment has sworn</p>\n<p>allegiance. In addition, characters from this regiment cannot</p>\n<p>purchase the Munitorum Influence Talent, although the GM</p>\n<p>may, at his discretion, make a functionally equivalent Talent</p>\n<p>available in its place (such as Severan Dominate Influence).</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"enemiesoftheimperium","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"drawback","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"1gXtS8Prd8WWQMrn"}
{"name":"Escalating Rage","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Passive</p>\n<p>Effect: While the Bulwark is in a Frenzy, whenever an enemy inflicts Critical Damage upon an ally within 10 metres or hits</p>\n<p>a Comrade within 10 metres, the Bulwark increases the value of his Unnatural Strength and Unnatural Toughness Traits by</p>\n<p>+1 until the end of the encounter. These Traits cannot exceed Unnatural Strength (8) and Unnatural Toughness (8) this way.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"escalatingrage","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"bulwark","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"8EyzY1RCUD93E3yr"}
{"name":"Weak Spot","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Full Action</p>\n<p>Effect: The Longshooter&rsquo;s Comrade fires a shot to weaken the target&rsquo;s armour so that he can pierce it with a second</p>\n<p>round placed on exactly the same location. The next time the Longshooter makes a Called Shot Action this Turn, he</p>\n<p>increases the Penetration of his weapon by X, where X is equal to the number of Degrees of Success he scores on the</p>\n<p>Ballistic Skill Test for the attack. His Comrade must be within communication range for him to issue this Order.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"weakspot","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"longshooter","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"8rrBjVzI7FXNOSCk"}
{"name":"Blatant Theft","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Order (Half Action)</p>\n<p>Effect: The Trailblazer&rsquo;s partner in crime bumps into their mark, disorienting him so that the Trailblazer can slip in</p>\n<p>and out undetected. The Trailblazer makes a Opposed Challenging (+0) Sleight of Hand Test, opposed by the</p>\n<p>Awareness of a single target within 3 metres. If the target is Unaware of the Trailblazer, he gains a +30 bonus to this</p>\n<p>Test. If he succeeds, the Trailblazer may steal one item (which cannot be larger than Size [2]) from the target&rsquo;s person. If</p>\n<p>he succeeds by three or more Degrees of Success, he and his Comrade may immediately make a Disengage Action as a</p>\n<p>Free Action after undertaking this Order. His Comrade must be within Cohesion for him to issue this Order.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"blatanttheft","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"trailblazer","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Apb0HVGpi18lcED3"}
{"name":"Hopelessly Primitive","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>No matter how long they fight in</p>\n<p>the Imperial Guard, the warriors of this regiment just cannot</p>\n<p>overcome their primitive ways and adapt to the advanced</p>\n<p>weaponry of the Imperial Guard. Characters from this regiment</p>\n<p>suffer a &ndash;5 penalty to Ballistic Skill and Weapon Skill Tests</p>\n<p>when using any weapon that is not from the Low-Tech</p>\n<p>weapons group, even if they possess the proper</p>\n<p>Talent to wield the weapon.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"hopelesslyprimitive","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"drawback","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"CczIZeTWCa8PBu5q"}
{"name":"Soldiers of the Omnissiah","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>The Lathe Worlds Home World</p>\n<p>represents a uniquely specific origin for a regiment. Such</p>\n<p>forces are not truly Imperial Guard regiments at all, and so do</p>\n<p>not include the Support Specialists associated with Imperial</p>\n<p>Guard regiments. Lathe Worlds characters cannot select the</p>\n<p>Commissar, Ministorum Priest, Ogryn, Ratling, Sanctioned</p>\n<p>Psyker, or Storm Trooper Specialities (they can select the</p>\n<p>Tech-Priest Enginseer Speciality). A Character from this</p>\n<p>regiment always count as both a Tech-Priest Enginseer and a</p>\n<p>Guardsman for the purposes of prerequisites, regardless of his</p>\n<p>current Speciality or Advanced Speciality. If a group wishes to</p>\n<p>include Support Specialists other than Tech-Priest Enginseers</p>\n<p>in a Lathe Worlds Squad, players should use the rules for</p>\n<p>Mixed Regiments presented in the O nly W ar supplement,</p>\n<p>h ammer Of the e mperOr</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"soldiersoftheomnissiah","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"lathe","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"CsOGezIL1UPI05kF"}
{"name":"Bonded to the Machine Cult","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>The regiment gains an additional</p>\n<p>+10 on all Logistics Tests to obtain Plasma, Melta, and</p>\n<p>Power weapons, and other items of advanced technology at</p>\n<p>the GM&rsquo;s discretion.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"bttmc","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"doctrine","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"EQMVEWN7WmxQVYnc"}
{"name":"Officially Nonexistent","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Whenever a unit from this regiment</p>\n<p>rolls doubles on a Logistics Test, the Test counts as failed,</p>\n<p>even if the score would normally have been successful, as</p>\n<p>the Departmento Munitorum denies the request from a</p>\n<p>nonexistent regiment or freezes it in bureaucratic tape.</p>\n<p>In addition, the GM should include additional Mission</p>\n<p>Complications in most missions to represent the confusion</p>\n<p>caused by the regiment&rsquo;s unusual status.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"officiallynonexistent","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"drawback","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"F0wWiuStbMCMfdWd"}
{"name":"The Touch of the Warp","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>For whatever reason, the soldiers</p>\n<p>of this regiment carry a spiritual and physical corruption,</p>\n<p>which manifests in horrific ways. Characters from this</p>\n<p>regiment begin play with 1d10 Corruption Points. In</p>\n<p>addition, characters from this regiment suffer an additional</p>\n<p>&ndash;10 penalty to Malignancy Tests and Tests to avoid gaining</p>\n<p>Mutations (see page 309 of the Only War Core Rulebook).</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"thetouchofthewarp","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"drawback","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"IqztfHUyIISEX5Ey"}
{"name":"Feigned Flank","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Sweeping Order (Free Action) (see Sweeping Orders on page 110)</p>\n<p>Effect: The Fixer can have any number of his Comrades within communication range participate in this Order. At</p>\n<p>the beginning of a Combat Encounter, so long as he is not Surprised, the Fixer may make a Difficult (&ndash;10) Deceive</p>\n<p>Test with a +10 bonus for each Comrade participating in this Order, Opposed by each enemy&rsquo;s Scrutiny. Each foe</p>\n<p>who loses this Opposed Test suffers a penalty to his Initiative equal to the number of Degrees of Success by which</p>\n<p>the Fixer won the Opposed Test.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"feignedflank","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"fixer","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"JnoyjMK4VKprbGDR"}
{"name":"Demolitionists","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Due to their training and experience, characters</p>\n<p>from a demolitionists regiment gain an additional +10</p>\n<p>bonuses to Tech-Use Tests made for the Demolitions special</p>\n<p>use of the Skill.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"demolitionists","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"doctrine","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"JxpqX7c9ClcjwgPo"}
{"name":"Stir, Spirits of Iron!","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Full Action</p>\n<p>Effect: While the Architectus Magna is linked with a multi-passenger vehicle via his mind impulse unit, so long as his Servitor</p>\n<p>is also within the vehicle, he can call upon it to temporarily enhance one of the vehicle&rsquo;s systems. The Architectus Magna</p>\n<p>makes a Challenging (+0) Tech-Use Test; if he succeeds, he can either boost the vehicle&rsquo;s engines or overcharge one of its</p>\n<p>weapons. If he chooses to enhance its engines, he increases the vehicle&rsquo;s Manoeuvrability by +5 per Degree of Success; if he</p>\n<p>decides to enhance a weapon, he increases the Damage of that weapon by +1 per Degree of Success. This effect persists for a</p>\n<p>number of Rounds equal to his Intelligence Bonus. He can only use this ability once per combat encounter.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"stirspiritsofiron","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"architectus magna","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"KyXzywkXeHbDZndC"}
{"name":"In the Shadows of the Ecclesiarchy's Light","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Rightfully or no, the</p>\n<p>Ecclesiarchy views this</p>\n<p>regiment with suspicion,</p>\n<p>seeing their religious</p>\n<p>practices (or lack</p>\n<p>thereof) as dangerously</p>\n<p>iconoclastic. Characters from</p>\n<p>this regiment suffer a &ndash;10</p>\n<p>penalty to all interaction tests</p>\n<p>with the representatives of</p>\n<p>the Ecclesiarchy. For such</p>\n<p>regiments, it is common for the</p>\n<p>Adeptus Ministorum to attach</p>\n<p>additional Priests, Confessors,</p>\n<p>and other representatives,</p>\n<p>particularly if they feel</p>\n<p>the regiment is not</p>\n<p>yet beyond salvation.</p>\n<p>However, such forces are sure to experience problems dealing</p>\n<p>with the regiment. Player Characters with the Ministorum</p>\n<p>Priest Speciality suffer a &ndash;10 penalty when interacting</p>\n<p>with NPC members of this regiment, including Comrades,</p>\n<p>but excluding the Ministorum Priest&rsquo;s own Comrade (it is</p>\n<p>assumed that his Comrade is either one of the few in the</p>\n<p>regiment loyal to the Ecclesiarchy&rsquo;s teachings, or is also</p>\n<p>an outsider). At his discretion, the GM might additionally</p>\n<p>apply this penalty to other PCs with ties to the Ecclesiarchy.</p>\n<p>The GM is encouraged to introduce additional narrative</p>\n<p>complications based on the specific nature of the regiment&rsquo;s</p>\n<p>relationship with the Adeptus Ministorum.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"itsotel","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"drawback","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"L9Kn5h00is305bZ5"}
{"name":"Coordinated Algorithms","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Passive</p>\n<p>Effect: The Enginseer Prime optimises his Servitors to assist him in tandem, each mechanical minion acting a cog within</p>\n<p>a greater machine. When two or more Servitors assist him on a Tech-Use Test via the Servo-Arm Comrade Advance (see</p>\n<p>page 99 of the O nly W ar Core Rulebook), he gains an additional +5 bonus for each Servitor that assists beyond the first.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"coordinatedalgorithms","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"enginseer prime","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"LplVjfiiF20Nhka4"}
{"name":"Virtuous Ignorance","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>The citizens of shrine worlds learn</p>\n<p>many lessons in virtue from the pious sermons and teachings</p>\n<p>of the Ecclesiarchy. Amongst these is the lesson that ignorance</p>\n<p>is a virtue not easily disdained by the wise. Heresy, blasphemy,</p>\n<p>and death are the just rewards of curiosity, for those who</p>\n<p>look beyond the teachings of the Adeptus Ministorum for</p>\n<p>knowledge walk a dangerous path. Due to their wise and</p>\n<p>wilful narrowness of mind, shrine world characters suffer a</p>\n<p>&ndash;10 penalty on all Forbidden Lore Tests.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"virtuousignorance","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"shrine","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"LvK5Bj9PGWqiLrtY"}
{"name":"Rite of Synchronised Steel","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Passive</p>\n<p>Effect: While the Architectus Magna is linked with a vehicle via his mind impulse unit, he may use his Intelligence</p>\n<p>Characteristic in place of his Agility Characteristic for Operate (Surface), Operate (Aeronautica), and Operate (Voidship)</p>\n<p>Tests. Whenever the vehicle suffers Critical Damage while the Architectus Magna is linked this way, he gains 1 level of</p>\n<p>Fatigue from the associated mental strain.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"riteofsynchronisedsteel","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"architectus magna","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"N17BSQpqxnPeiXQA"}
{"name":"Annnihilate Them!","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Full Action</p>\n<p>Effect: The Praecentor of Penance can have any number of Comrades beyond the first within Cohesion participate in</p>\n<p>this Order. As part of this Order, he makes a Difficult (&ndash;10) Command Test with a +10 bonus for each Comrade</p>\n<p>participating in this Order. If he succeeds, his Comrades rush forward with him and he cannot be targeted by melee</p>\n<p>attacks while making a Charge Action until the end of his Turn. Further, for every Degree of Success he scores on</p>\n<p>the Test, the Praecentor of Penance inflicts one additional hit with a melee weapon wielded by one or more of his</p>\n<p>Comrades upon the target of any Charge Action he makes until the end of his Turn.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"annihilatethem","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"praecentor of penance","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"P1hgvpSoaw2GcoW4"}
{"name":"Improved Dexterity","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Passive</p>\n<p>Effect: The Bone &lsquo;ead can wield Basic and Thrown ranged weapons and Melee weapons as though he did not have the</p>\n<p>Clumsy Trait. Further, thanks to his massive size, the Bone &rsquo;ead can wield these weapons in one hand without penalty,</p>\n<p>even if they normally require both hands.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"improveddexterity","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"bone 'ead","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Ra8DnMbwcPQ0lOhW"}
{"name":"Brutal Encouragement","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Half Action</p>\n<p>Effect: Ogryns delight in the havoc that a Bone &lsquo;ead can wreak, and the &ldquo;little &rsquo;uns&rdquo; who accompany them into the field</p>\n<p>usually take solace in the fact that such a powerful and savage warrior is on their side. The Bone &lsquo;ead&rsquo;s Comrade lets out an</p>\n<p>enthusiastic cry as the Ogryn slams into some terrifying foe, encouraging him and the other soldiers nearby to redouble their</p>\n<p>efforts. Until the end of the Turn, whenever the Bone &lsquo;ead kills an enemy, he may make a Challenging (+0) Intimidate</p>\n<p>Test as a Free Action. If he succeeds, each ally within communication range of the Bone &lsquo;ead&rsquo;s Comrade gains a +10 bonus to</p>\n<p>the next Weapon Skill or Ballistic Skill Test he makes before the end of the next Turn. Further, each Ogryn affected by this</p>\n<p>ability may enter a Frenzy as a Free Action (see the Frenzy Talent on page 144 of the O nly W ar Core Rulebook).</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"brutalencouragement","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"bone 'ead","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Rrzh7wgm8uo63quw"}
{"name":"Isolated by Machines(Lathe World)","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Lathe Worlds characters are selected</p>\n<p>for a life of war at a young age, dedicating their lives to the</p>\n<p>defence of the Adeptus Mechanicus&rsquo; interests in the Calixis</p>\n<p>Sector. The warriors of the Crimson Guard and other Lathe</p>\n<p>Worlds forces are unforgiving, blunt, and seem harsh to</p>\n<p>those unfamiliar with the cold, logical way the Adeptus</p>\n<p>Mechanicus operates. Lathe Worlds characters often</p>\n<p>relate to machines and servitors more readily than their</p>\n<p>flesh and blood counterparts, and have a tendency</p>\n<p>toward jargon and filling their conversations with</p>\n<p>long strings of Techna-Lingua that are nearly unintelligible</p>\n<p>to the average trooper. Lathe Worlds characters suffer a</p>\n<p>&ndash;10 penalty to any Interaction Tests made to interact with</p>\n<p>characters who are not also from a Lathe World, forge world,</p>\n<p>or are initiates of the Adeptus Mechanicus.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"isolatedbymachines","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"lathe","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"SFrL88p3vl1eTV3W"}
{"name":"Unwilling","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>This regiment was forcibly conscripted, perhaps</p>\n<p>at gun point, and its members serve the Imperial Guard</p>\n<p>only grudgingly. Characters from this regiment suffer a &ndash;10</p>\n<p>penalty to all Willpower Tests, and all Command Tests to</p>\n<p>influence members of this regiment (including Comrades)</p>\n<p>suffer a &ndash;10 penalty.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"unwilling","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"drawback","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"TDmVepwIPGAzYKAf"}
{"name":"Enhanced Intellect","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Passive</p>\n<p>Effect: Bone &rsquo;eads are usually more articulate than their rough brethren, and can thus communicate their needs much</p>\n<p>more efficiently to non-Ogryns. Further, the Comrades of these warriors frequently grow accustomed to their guttural,</p>\n<p>simple language. The Bone &lsquo;ead gains a +10 bonus to Tests to activate Orders that he gives to his Comrade.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"enhancedintellect","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"bone 'ead","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"WQAt57vZgmRTLIP6"}
{"name":"Shattering Blow","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Passive</p>\n<p>Effect: While the Bulwark is in a Frenzy, whenever he inflicts Righteous Fury with a Melee Attack, he also inflicts a</p>\n<p>hit on each other target within a number of metres equal to his Strength Bonus (other than himself) with the following</p>\n<p>profile: 1d10+SB I; Pen 0; Concussive.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"shatteringblow","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"bulwark","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"WbzI0jJLPzkmgOOF"}
{"name":"Convenient Distraction","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Order (Half Action)</p>\n<p>Effect: The Trailblazer calls upon his Comrade to distract his opponent, giving him a chance to dart to an advantageous</p>\n<p>position. The Trailblazer makes an Opposed Challenging (+0) Stealth Test, Opposed by the Awareness of each</p>\n<p>enemy within 10 metres. If the Ratling wins the Opposed Test against a target, that target counts as being Unaware</p>\n<p>of him until the end of his next Turn. His Comrade must be within communication range for him to issue this Order.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"convenientdistraction","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"trailblazer","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"YajUvfpPyG8MuSsT"}
{"name":"Piety's Reward","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Passive</p>\n<p>Effect: Whenever an ally within communication range of the Prelate-at-Arms&rsquo; Comrade spends a Fate Point, he becomes</p>\n<p>invigorated by the act of pious labour. The Prelate-at-Arms may make a Hard (&ndash;20) Command Test as a Free Action;</p>\n<p>if he succeeds, he may issue the Righteous Oration Order until the end of his next Turn even if his Comrade has already</p>\n<p>used it once this Encounter.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"pietysreward","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"prelate-at-arms","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Zg8MOEo7b0JjMoNO"}
{"name":"Ill-Omened","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Characters born aboard void stations often</p>\n<p>seem unusual to those from the firm ground of a planet. Life</p>\n<p>amongst the machinery and cramped corridors of a void</p>\n<p>station is quite different to life beneath an open sky, and is</p>\n<p>confining even by the standards of a hive world. Additionally,</p>\n<p>void born characters are often appear unnaturally pale and</p>\n<p>gaunt. This unwholesome air, combined with the insular,</p>\n<p>clannish ways of many void born, often causes difficulties</p>\n<p>when interacting with non-void born regiments. Void born</p>\n<p>characters suffer a &ndash;10 penalty to Interaction Tests made to</p>\n<p>interact with characters who are not also void born.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"illomened","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"void","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"a1zCgKvh6trLod1p"}
{"name":"Guiding Fire","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Full Action</p>\n<p>Effect: The Gun Lugger&rsquo;s Comrade lays down a trail of shots to a chosen target that the Gun Lugger himself can attempt</p>\n<p>to mimic. Until the end of the Turn, the Gun Lugger doubles his Degrees of Success on any Ballistic Skill Test he makes</p>\n<p>to hit the target his Comrade marked. The Gun Lugger&rsquo;s Comrade must be within Cohesion for him to enact this Order.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"guidingfire","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"gun lugger","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"aPn4qrtfaQLm2LTT"}
{"name":"Gather the Penitents","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Passive</p>\n<p>Effect: The Praecentor of Penance gains an extra Comrade. He can select this Advance a number of times up to his</p>\n<p>Fellowship Bonus. See the Multiple Comrades Sidebar on page 55.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"X","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"gatherthepenitents","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"praecentor of penance","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"bkaitbnBvaMruJEr"}
{"name":"Do not Falter!","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Half Action</p>\n<p>Effect: The Prelate-at-Arms&rsquo; Comrade calls for his allies to ignore the odds and fight on in the Emperor&rsquo;s name! Until the</p>\n<p>end of the Turn, whenever the Prelate-at-Arms uses the Inspire Special Use of the Command Skill, each ally affected by this</p>\n<p>ability gains an additional +20 bonus to Tests to resist the effects of Fear, Pinning, and mind-altering Psychic Powers until</p>\n<p>the end of his next Turn. The Prelate-at-Arms&rsquo; Comrade must be within communication range for him to issue this Order.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"donotfalter","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"prelate-at-arms","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"frj1orKj8rsmQUfm"}
{"name":"Target Lock","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Full Action</p>\n<p>Effect: The Crimson Exemplar&rsquo;s Servitor marks a target for annihilation, synchronising with the Crimson Exemplar&rsquo;s</p>\n<p>integrated weapons and allowing him to strike at his target with all of them. Once per encounter, the Crimson Exemplar</p>\n<p>may issue this Order and make a Challenging (+0) Intelligence Test and spend his Full Action as part of the Order; if</p>\n<p>he succeeds, he inflicts a single hit on a target within range with one of his weapons, plus an additional hit with another one</p>\n<p>of his weapons on a target within range for each Degree of Success he scored beyond the first. Each weapon can only inflict</p>\n<p>a single hit this way. The Crimson Exemplar&rsquo;s Servitor must be within communication range for him to issue this Order.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"targetlock","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"crimson exemplar","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"gEKMO2WhbOV0PhpN"}
{"name":"Notorious Pilferer","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Full Action</p>\n<p>Effect: Once per Game Session, the Trailblazer may have his Comrade produce a single, previously unmentioned item</p>\n<p>with an Availability of Common or more available from his stash of &ldquo;borrowed&rdquo; sundries. The Trailblazer can only</p>\n<p>acquire items that the Game Master deems reasonable in this way, and there are naturally consequences for filching from</p>\n<p>certain prominent individuals. His Comrade must be within Cohesion for him to issue this Order.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"notoriouspilferer","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"trailblazer","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"gzXxn6cvM7yO71ZO"}
{"name":"Blazing Exemplar","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Half Action</p>\n<p>Effect: Until the end of the Turn, whenever the Incinerant Priest inflicts Righteous Fury on an enemy, each ally within</p>\n<p>Cohesion range of his Comrade gains the following bonus: this character inflicts Righteous Fury on a result of 9 or 10</p>\n<p>on Damage rolls until the end of his next Turn. The Incinerant Priest can only issue this Order so long as his Comrade</p>\n<p>is within Cohesion Range.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"blazingexemplar","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"incinerant priest","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"hfcYD0tpGhluywLX"}
{"name":"Walking Archive","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Passive</p>\n<p>Effect: When assisted by his Comrade, the Rector Erudite gains a +20 bonus to all Common Lore, Forbidden Lore,</p>\n<p>Linguistics, and Scholastic Lore Tests.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"walkingarchive","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"rector erudite","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"htZLMMUcIdWEROp7"}
{"name":"Helping Hands","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Passive</p>\n<p>Effect: The Fixer gains an extra Comrade. He can select this Advance up to a number of times equal to his Fellowship</p>\n<p>Bonus. See the Multiple Comrades Sidebar on page 55.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"X","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"helpinghands","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"fixer","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ic0M8Pc9pqjRL7Ge"}
{"name":"Void Accustomed","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Void born characters have experience</p>\n<p>moving about in zero-gravity environments, whether by dint</p>\n<p>of special training, mechanical failures, or the simple necessities</p>\n<p>of life on an orbital station. Void born characters do not treat</p>\n<p>zero gravity as Difficult Terrain. In addition, the Agility Test to</p>\n<p>stay on-target when making a Charge or Run Action in zero</p>\n<p>gravity is only Difficult (&ndash;10) for void born characters.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"voidaccustomed","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"void","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"khMuwn3T0eRplSbl"}
{"name":"Countersnipe","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Full Action</p>\n<p>Effect: The Longshooter&rsquo;s Comrade keeps careful watch over the field, subtly alerting his partner to any oncoming</p>\n<p>danger. Until the beginning of his next Turn, the Longshooter may spend a Reaction to make a Standard Ranged</p>\n<p>Attack Action with a &ndash;20 penalty against a single foe within range who targets him with a Ranged Attack. If he kills</p>\n<p>or incapacitates his target with his Reaction, the incoming attack automatically misses the Longshooter; otherwise, the</p>\n<p>attack strikes or misses him as normal. His Comrade must be within Cohesion for him to issue this Order.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"countersnipe","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"longshooter","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ksqtcwbfV8MVrbNg"}
{"name":"Know the Heretic; Kill the Heretic!","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Full Action</p>\n<p>Effect: Once per encounter, the Rector Erudite may issue this Order, choose a type of enemy (such as Orks, Eldar,</p>\n<p>Chaos worshippers, or any other that the Game Master deems appropriate) and make an Hard (&ndash;20) Common Lore,</p>\n<p>Forbidden Lore, or Scholastic Lore Test for a Specialisation of one of these Skills that includes the chosen foe. If he</p>\n<p>succeeds, each ally within communication range of his Comrade may re-roll one missed attack per Round against the</p>\n<p>chosen foe for a number of Rounds equal to his Degrees of Success on the Test.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"kthkth","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"rector erudite","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"lG981wgLKHNw2yPS"}
{"name":"Armour of Faith","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&nbsp;Once per session, when a shrine world</p>\n<p>character gains any number of Corruption Points, the character</p>\n<p>may spend a Fate Point to instead gain no Corruption Points</p>\n<p>from that source.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"armouroffaith","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"shrine","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"msbOYu4cCpVPfxu9"}
{"name":"Redundant Systems","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Passive</p>\n<p>Effect: The Enginseer Prime gains an extra Servitor. He can select this Advance up to a number of times equal to his</p>\n<p>Intelligence Bonus. See the Multiple Comrades Sidebar on page 55.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"X","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"redundantsystems","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"enginseer prime","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ndF6mdE9oAarJ7V4"}
{"name":"Ballistic Fury","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Passive</p>\n<p>Effect: The Gun Lugger can wield Heavy ranged weapons that do not have the Ogryn-Proof Quality as though he did not</p>\n<p>have the Clumsy Trait. However, whenever a ranged weapon without the Ogryn-Proof Quality the Gun Lugger is wielding</p>\n<p>Jams, the Gun Lugger breaks the weapon in his exuberance unless his Comrade is within Cohesion to calm him. A broken</p>\n<p>weapon must be repaired with a Hard (&ndash;20) Tech-Use Test that requires at least several minutes before it can be fired again.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"ballisticfury","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"gun lugger","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ohQYWB3akWIdcX0w"}
{"name":"Sappers","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Sappers are trained to both build</p>\n<p>and disassemble fortifications, undermine</p>\n<p>walls, and similar duties. Characters from</p>\n<p>this regiment gain a +10 bonus to Tech-</p>\n<p>Use and Trade (Technomat) Tests to</p>\n<p>construct or disassemble a structure.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"sappers","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"doctrine","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"sr3bgPGnyIyx9Gqx"}
{"name":"Integrated Weapons System","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Passive</p>\n<p>Effect: The Crimson Guard are known for their extensive augmentations and the powerful integrated weapons that</p>\n<p>draw energy from their bodies. When a Crimson Exemplar buys this Advance, he chooses one of his Basic or Melee</p>\n<p>weapons to become an integrated weapon. That weapon is now built into his body (grafted to one of his limbs, mounted</p>\n<p>on a mechanical appendage, or otherwise attached), and can only be removed with a Hard (&ndash;20) Tech-Use Test. If the</p>\n<p>weapon required ammunition, it draws its power from the Crimson Exemplar&rsquo;s potentia coil and no longer requires fresh</p>\n<p>ammunition when reloaded, but the Crimson Exemplar gains 1 level of Fatigue every time he reloads it. The Crimson</p>\n<p>Exemplar may select this Advance a number of times equal to his Toughness Bonus.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"X","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"integratedweaponsystem","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"crimson exemplar","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"u5R2QVGqN2ptNeHA"}
{"name":"Reliquary","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>One reliquary per squad. The</p>\n<p>reliquary might take any number of forms, from a simple</p>\n<p>wooden box to an elaborate triptych or golden sarcophagus.</p>\n<p>What is important however, is the reliquary&rsquo;s contents&mdash;either</p>\n<p>some portion of the bodily remains of a saint or another object</p>\n<p>of great religious significance for the worshipers of the Emperor.</p>\n<p>Depending on the reliquary&rsquo;s size, it might take only a single</p>\n<p>person to carry, or five or more, but typically two characters</p>\n<p>(including Comrades) must carry it. As long as the reliquary</p>\n<p>remains in the Squad&rsquo;s possession, all Squad Members gain</p>\n<p>a +10 bonus to Willpower Tests and count as possessing the</p>\n<p>Unshakeable Faith Talent. In addition, the Player Characters</p>\n<p>reduce all Corruption Points gained by 1 to a minimum of 1.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"reliquary","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"doctrine","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"u6v8SVZodWAYEzNU"}
{"name":"Record Keeper","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Passive</p>\n<p>Effect: When assisted by his Comrade, the Rector Erudite gains a +20 bonus to any Intelligence Test to remember</p>\n<p>specific and highly detailed information from his Total Recall Talent.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"recordkeeper","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"rector erudite","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"uSHX3FIcc4hTaVsU"}
{"name":"Bravado and Bluster","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Passive</p>\n<p>Effect: When the Fixer makes a Charm, Deceive, or Intimidate Test while assisted by one or more Comrades, he gains</p>\n<p>a +10 bonus for each Comrade assisting him.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"bravadoandbluster","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"fixer","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"xl30TFtL7Swjhgej"}
{"name":"Waste of Ressources","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Due to flagrant misuse</p>\n<p>or neglect of whatever equipment it issues</p>\n<p>them, the Departmento Munitorum</p>\n<p>is loathe to assign any but the bare</p>\n<p>minimum of gear to this regiment.</p>\n<p>All Logistics Tests other than those</p>\n<p>made to obtain Low-Tech weapons</p>\n<p>suffer a &ndash;20 penalty.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"wasteofressources","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"drawback","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"yc72TmLZCRZPyYBs"}
{"name":"Brimstone Rhetoric","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Passive</p>\n<p>Effect: The Incinerant Priest&rsquo;s Comrade stokes the fires of hatred in the hearts of his allies, driving them on to incinerate</p>\n<p>the heretic, the xenos, and the witch. Whenever an ally (including the Incinerant Priest) within Cohesion range of the</p>\n<p>Incinerant Priest&rsquo;s Comrade inflicts Righteous Fury on an enemy with an attack that causes Damage, he rolls 1d5 twice</p>\n<p>on the appropriate Critical Hit Table and discards the lower result.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"brimstonerhetoric","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"incinerant priest","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"yxtCprB4Kvpq6158"}
{"name":"Machine Lord","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Full Action</p>\n<p>Effect: The Enginseer Prime can assume precise control over his Servitors, using them to strike down his foes. Once</p>\n<p>during each of his Turns, the Enginseer Prime may make a Challenging (+0) Tech-Use Test as a Half Action. If he</p>\n<p>succeeds, he can have up to one of his Servitors, plus one additional Servitor per Degree of Success he scores beyond the</p>\n<p>first, make a Half Action Melee Attack Action or Ranged Attack Action against a target within range. For this attack, the</p>\n<p>Servitor uses the Enginseer Prime&rsquo;s Weapon Skill or Ballistic Skill in place of its own relevant Characteristic.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"machinelord","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"enginseer prime","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"zwrdXADi5o89YPw6"}
